Unknown gunmen have killed two police officers and four other people in an attack on a moving bus at Idema-Otuabagi road in Ogbia Local Council of Bayelsa State.  MEANWHILE, the state Police Command has warned miscreants and hoodlums, who may want to hijack the procession of the Ijaws during the Boro’s Day celebration to desist as policemen are strategically positioned to ensure a hitch-free event.
 
The Commissioner of Police, who felicitated with the Ijaws on the occasion, re-assured members of the public of adequate security and urged them to unite for peace and progress of the country.